06409nam a22009855i 9783110944754DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20122008gw     fo  d z      ger d  a97831109447547 a10.1515/97831109447542doi  a(DE-B1597)46106  a(OCoLC)979589225  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 7aLIT0000002bisacsh04a801.95  aEC 22002rvk0(DE-625)rvk/20477:00aRückkehr des Autors :bZur Erneuerung eines umstrittenen Begriffs /chrsg. von Fotis Jannidis, Simone Winko, Matias Martinez, Gerhard Lauer. 1aTübingen : bMax Niemeyer Verlag, c[2012] 4c©2008  a1 online resource (553 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStudien und Texte zur Sozialgeschichte der Literatur ,x0174-4410 ;v710 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDie Theoriedebatte hat den Autor für obsolet erklärt; in der Praxis dagegen werden legitime Verwendungsweisen des Autorkonzepts immer wieder demonstriert. Diese Diskrepanz deutet an, daß die theoretische Reflexion über den Autor zentralen Formen des wissenschaftlichen Umgangs mit Literatur nicht gerecht wird. Die Beiträge des Bandes versuchen unter historischer wie unter systematischer Perspektive den begriffsgeschichtlichen Hintergrund des Autorkonzepts genau zu rekonstruieren, die Idealtypen der Verwendung und die in der Praxis entstehenden Problemmuster zu analysieren. Außer Texten werden auch andere Medien wie Film, Musik, Kunst und Hypertexte untersucht.  aTheoretical debate has declared the author obsolete. In practice, however, certain usages of the author concept are repeatedly demonstrated as being legitimate. This discrepancy suggests that theoretical reflection on the author fails to do justice to central forms of the scholarly approach to literature. The articles in this volume take both systematic and historical perspectives on this controversial term in an attempt to accurately reconstruct the history of the concept and to analyze the problem constellations generated by it in practice. The discussion also extends to non-literary media such as film, music, art, and hypertexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aAuthorshipvCongresses. 0aLiteraturexHistory and criticismvCongresses. 4aAutor. 4aBegriff. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBEIN, THOMAS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBURKE, SEÁN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBURROWS, JOHN F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBÜHLER, AXEL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDANNEBERG, LUTZ, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEIBL, KARL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJANNIDIS, FOTIS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJASZI, PETER, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJannidis, Fotis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKALERI, EKATERINI, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKAMP, WERNER, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKINDT, TOM, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLAUER, GERHARD, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLauer, Gerhard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMARTINDALE, COLIN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMARTINEZ, MATIAS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartinez, Matias, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMÜLLER, HANS-HARALD, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat